Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Spread 1 cup crushed potato chips evenly on bottom of casserole dish. Next, layer 1 can of tuna, half of the peas, and half of the soup. Place slices of cheese on top of this. Repeat layering with tuna, peas and soup. Finish with a layer of chips, and top with slices of cheese. Bake in preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until bubbly and golden brown.